ies. Bringing together an international range of contributors from the USA, Latin America, the UK and continental Europe, it explores the complex relationship between constitutional democracy and ‘the people’. Contributors explore this relationship through the lens of radical democracy, engaging with the work of key figures such as Hannah Arendt, Carl Schmitt, Claude Lefort and Jacques Rancière.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aConstitutional law. 0aDemocracy. 0aRepresentative government and representation. 4aLaw. 7aLAW / Constitutional.2bisacsh1 aArditi, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArvidsson, Matilda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrännström, Leila, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBrännström, Leila, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFalk, Hjalmar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGill-Pedro, Eduardo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirvonen, Ari, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLindroos-Hovinheimo, Susanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLukkari, Hanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMinkkinen, Panu, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMinkkinen, Panu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurpeinen, Juho, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVergara, Camila, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVinx, Lars, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWittrock, Jon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZakin, Emil